title: Megyn Kelly exposes sanctuary cities’ ‘BS’ law enforcement ‘lie’ to protect illegals
description: ‘The Megyn Kelly Show’ host Megyn Kelly has called out sanctuary cities over a “lie” about illegal immigrants and law enforcement.  “Sanctuary cities claiming – this is BS – but the claim they don’t want illegals to feel like they can’t call the cops, like if their husbands are beating them up,” she told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Like a woman is going to instead of get her husband off of her, she’s going to get deported.  “That has not been how law enforcement has been using those kinds of calls, just FYI, this is a lie, but that’s how they get away with it.”

title: Democrat and Republican’s fiery clash over Trump shakes committee hearing
description: Democratic Representative Maxine Waters has clashed with Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent over US President Donald Trump’s economic agenda.  The war of words came during a House Financial Services Committee hearing, where Bessent gave testimony.  Questions were asked to Bessent about Trump’s tariffs, where Waters demanded either yes or no answers from the Treasury Secretary.  In the fiery debate, the two exchanged harsh words, with Congresswoman Waters asking if someone could “shut” Bessent up.  Bessent replied, calling on her to “maintain some level of dignity”, where Representative French Hill exclaimed that Water’s time was up, resulting in her diverting her anger.

title: ‘Bad news’ for ‘woke American elitist’ Billie Eilish after Native American tribe calls singer out
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio has hit out at “woke American elitist” Billie Eilish over her anti-ICE speech in which she said that “no one is illegal on stolen land”.  “Well, uh oh, her claims of stolen land have been called out by the Native American tribe who claim her multi-million-dollar California mansion sits on their land,” she said.  “The Tongva tribe said they appreciate Eilish’s sentiment but noted that the performer hasn’t contacted them directly and insisted that next time, she explicitly reference them.”

title: Karoline Leavitt hilariously mocks Hollywood elites after Billie Elish’s Grammys humiliation
description: White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt has blasted the Hollywood elite who spoke out against the Trump administration at this years Grammy’s awards.

title: ‘Disgraced’ Andrew given ‘heave-ho’ out of Royal Lodge amid disturbing new Epstein allegations
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio claims Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor has been given the “heave-ho” out of Royal Lodge after more allegations came out against him in the Jeffrey Epstein files.  This comes amid claims a second woman was allegedly trafficked for Andrew.  The former prince has always denied any wrongdoing relating to his links with Epstein and has never been charged with any offence.

title: 'I'm a conservative at heart': Pauline Hanson open to future Coalition deal
description: Sky News Senior Political Reporter Trudy McIntosh claims One Nation Leader Pauline Hanson is “serious” about a future Coalition deal.

title: Senator Paterson ‘not anticipating’ spill motion, ‘supports’ Sussan Ley as leader
description: Shadow Finance Minister James Paterson claims he supports Sussan Ley’s leadership and is “not anticipating” a spill motion.  “If I advocate for a candidate or for a spill, the first person who would know before I did so would be Sussan Ley,” Mr Paterson told Sky News Australia.  “You can continue to safely assume that I support Sussan’s leadership.”

title: ‘Another one coming’: RBA expected to hike rates further to control inflation
description: EY Oceania Chief Economist Cherelle Murphy says the RBA is facing “quite a bit of pressure” to get inflation down.  Ms Murphy told Sky News Australia that the RBA’s forecast has two rate hikes already “considered”.  “So, I think yeah, we’ve got at least another one coming.”

title: ICE officers will now start wearing body cameras on immigration patrols
description: Sky News Washington analyst Annelise Nielsen says ICE agents are now having to wear body cameras on immigration patrols.   “The other concession that we have seen is they are now going to be putting body cameras on all of these agents as well,” Ms Neilsen told Sky News Australia.  “That’s not a requirement for federal agents, but it is becoming an increasing concern as you see these activities.”

title: Sydney man sentenced over death threats sent to Jewish group avoids jail
description: A Sydney man has avoided jail time after sending death threats to a Jewish group and New South Wales independent MP Alex Greenwich.

title: NBC's Savannah Guthrie breaks down during emotional plea for return of her missing mother
description: NBC ‘Today’ co-host Savannah Guthrie has given an emotional plea for the return of her missing mother, Nancy Guthrie.  Joined alongside family, they expressed that they heard there was a “ransom note” but could not confirm, expressing that in this day and age, things could be manipulated.  Nancy Guthrie, aged 84, was last seen at her Tucson residence in Arizona, according to the Pima County Sheriff’s Department.  Speaking directly to the alleged kidnappers, the family said they were “ready to talk” but need to know “without a doubt” Nancy Guthrie is alive.  “We, too, have heard the reports about a ransom letter in the media. As a family, we are doing everything that we can … however, we live in a world where voices and images are easily manipulated,” Savannah said.

title: Thousands of violent illegal immigrants arrested in brutal Minnesota crackdown
description: The Department of Homeland Security says federal law enforcement has arrested more than 4,000 violent illegal immigrants in Minnesota.  This is under Operation Metro Surge, which is targeting murderers, rapists, gang members and terrorists.  DHS officials said arrests have continued despite violent resistance from protesters and called on local “sanctuary” politicians to cooperate.  White House press secretary Karoline Leavitt praised President Trump’s enforcement policies.  "President Trump’s commonsense immigration enforcement policies are delivering the public safety results the American people demanded, with more than 4,000 dangerous criminal illegal aliens already arrested in Minnesota since Operation Metro began," Leavitt told Fox News Digital.  Federal officials vowed not to “back down” from their mission to remove criminal illegal aliens from American neighbourhoods.

title: Melania Trump brutally shuts down CNN reporter over question about Ghislaine Maxwell
description: First Lady Melania Trump has shut down a CNN reporter’s question related to Jeffrey Epstein’s accomplice, Ghislaine Maxwell.  On Wednesday, Melania welcomed reporters to the White House as she met with American-Israeli Keith Siegel and his wife, Aviva.  The couple’s visit marked the anniversary of Keith’s release from Hamas captivity following America’s ceasefire agreement.  Following the meeting, CNN’s Betsy Klein asked the First Lady about Maxwell’s possible move to a high-security prison.  “We are here celebrating the release and the life of these two incredible people. So let's honour that, thank you,” Melania fired back.

title: PM to head to Indonesia to sign new security arrangement
description: Australia and Indonesia will confront regional challenges together following the formal signing of a new security arrangement.  Prime Minister Anthony Albanese will travel to Indonesia on Thursday afternoon to make it official.  This is Mr Albanese’s fifth visit to Jakarta as leader and his third bilateral meeting with Indonesian President Prabowo Subianto in the past year.

title: ‘Embarrassment’: Conservative side of politics continues ‘tearing itself apart’
description: Principle Advisory Managing Partner Ryan Liddell weighs in on the recent Coalition fallout.   “It’s almost embarrassing what’s happening on the conservative side of politics,” Mr Liddell told Sky News Australia.  “You look at the Liberal Party tearing itself apart, you look at the Nats running away having a hissy fit, they're trying to tear themselves apart.  “It’s an absolute embarrassment.”
